 {"id":"beads_rust-dgo2","title":"[MEDIUM] Security hygiene: harden installer verification and import path handling","description":"Phase 3 security audit bundle for CLI security surfaces. No CRITICAL/HIGH finding was confirmed; these are concrete MEDIUM/LOW hardening items worth scheduling together.

Audit targets traced:
- install.sh: download_release downloads release archive, optionally downloads <archive>.sha256, warns and continues when checksum is unavailable, and also accepts checksum verification when no sha256sum/shasum tool exists by setting actual=expected. Attack vector: a compromised proxy/CA, tampered custom artifact URL, or release asset served without its checksum can result in an unverified br binary being installed. Fix direction: fail closed for official release artifacts unless a valid checksum is available and a hash tool runs; require an explicit --insecure-skip-checksum style override for development/custom artifacts.
- install.sh: tar/zip archives are extracted into $TMP before member paths are validated. Attack vector: malicious artifact with absolute or parent-directory archive entries may write outside the extraction root on extractors that honor them, then installer searches for the first executable named br. Fix direction: list and reject archive members with absolute paths, .. components, symlinks, or hardlinks before extraction; extract into a nested directory and install only the expected binary path.
- install.sh: optional gum/rustup paths perform network installation and sudo package-manager/repo setup for convenience. Attack vector: interactive install can execute third-party installer/repo steps before br is installed, including privileged package-manager changes for gum. Fix direction: make cosmetic gum installation opt-in or no-sudo by default; document rustup separately or require explicit confirmation outside easy mode.
- src/util/markdown_import.rs: parse_markdown_file rejects lexical .. and checks the apparent .md/.markdown extension, but reads with fs::read_to_string without rejecting symlinks or canonicalizing to an intended workspace. Attack vector: an untrusted repo can provide issues.md as a symlink to a local markdown file outside the repo; running br create --file issues.md imports private content into the issue DB/JSONL. Fix direction: reject symlink/non-regular inputs, or canonicalize and require the target under cwd/repo unless an explicit allow-external-file option is provided.
- src/sync/: sync path validation and atomic writes are strong for .beads containment and symlink rejection, but validation and subsequent reads remain separate operations. Attack vector: a local attacker with write access to .beads can race a validated JSONL input path before import reads it. Fix direction: where platform support allows, open with nofollow semantics and validate metadata after open; otherwise document local same-user race limitations.

Notes:
- src/mcp/ was audited for actor-name command injection and path traversal. Actor is persisted into IDs/events/storage calls and not fed to shell commands or filesystem paths; tool JSON schemas reject unknown properties and labels/IDs are validated on mutation. No high-severity MCP finding from this pass.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"beads_rust__p7","created_at":"2026-04-22T20:48:51.198129024Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T21:21:17.626610749Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T21:21:17.626247328Z","close_reason":"Hardened installer checksum/archive extraction and markdown import path handling; split remaining low-risk follow-ups into beads_rust-dhzk and beads_rust-uopk.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":344,"issue_id":"beads_rust-dgo2","author":"beads_rust__p7","text":"degraded-coordination: Agent Mail rejected AGENT_TAG as invalid identity; files: install.sh, src/util/markdown_import.rs, src/sync/path.rs","created_at":"2026-04-22T21:08:49Z"}]}
